WEBVTT

00:02.527 --> 00:04.486
♪ ♪

00:04.505 --> 00:06.213
Ho, ho, ho!

00:10.052 --> 00:11.385
(shrieks)

00:16.559 --> 00:18.308
(school bell rings)

00:21.022 --> 00:22.021
(grunts)

00:24.933 --> 00:27.084
-(bicycle bell rings)
-(barking)

00:27.186 --> 00:28.694
Merry Christmas!

00:28.887 --> 00:30.821
(electronic beeping)

00:32.575 --> 00:35.517
(munching)

00:35.578 --> 00:37.519
Oh, stupid Flanders.

00:37.538 --> 00:38.853
("game over" noise plays)

00:38.914 --> 00:39.913
D'oh!

00:47.923 --> 00:50.440
Oh, thanks for bringing me
up here, Dad.

00:50.459 --> 00:52.109
It's magnificent.

00:52.169 --> 00:54.553
Ugh, I could really use it
after what happened today.

00:54.746 --> 00:56.463
Aw, sweetie, are you still mad

00:56.557 --> 00:58.782
about that big dumb jerk
at school?

00:58.842 --> 01:00.225
She's my teacher.

01:00.418 --> 01:02.286
And her name is Miss Hoover.

01:02.304 --> 01:03.954
It's unforgivable what she did.

01:04.014 --> 01:05.305
What was it again?

01:05.399 --> 01:07.149
(groans)

01:09.653 --> 01:12.796
Breakfast!

01:12.856 --> 01:14.823
Here you go.

01:15.859 --> 01:17.317
Melon?! Ugh.

01:17.411 --> 01:19.152
Marge, no one dreams
of waking up

01:19.246 --> 01:21.154
to the sounds of frying melon.

01:21.248 --> 01:23.231
-Yeah, Marge.
-See?

01:23.250 --> 01:25.918
Your fruit breakfast has turned
him into a first name user.

01:26.111 --> 01:28.253
For once, could this family
start the day

01:28.446 --> 01:31.090
with fruit instead of
greasy animal fat?

01:31.283 --> 01:32.649
Even the dog is sweating grease.

01:32.751 --> 01:34.718
(barking)

01:37.214 --> 01:40.415
He'll be back for breakfast
and... (gasps) Oh, God!

01:40.518 --> 01:41.850
♪ ♪

01:43.795 --> 01:44.853
-(Marge gasps)
-We got her!

01:45.889 --> 01:47.189
(groans)

01:49.059 --> 01:52.093
I think I've got the answer.

01:52.154 --> 01:54.262
Mm-hmm. Gravy up your fruit,
boy?

01:54.323 --> 01:56.264
Look at me. I'm eating healthy.

01:56.325 --> 01:58.692
(gargling)

01:58.828 --> 02:00.119
(sighs) You win.

02:00.312 --> 02:01.453
I'll make bacon.

02:01.605 --> 02:03.180
Put away the gravy boat.

02:03.198 --> 02:05.940
They say the best days
of a gravy boat owner's life

02:06.001 --> 02:08.943
are the day you get it
and the day you get rid of it.

02:09.004 --> 02:10.337
(chuckles)

02:11.340 --> 02:13.114
No, Bart, stop!

02:13.175 --> 02:16.693
This is my mobile for my
"Who Inspires You?" project.

02:16.712 --> 02:20.305
Let me guess: it's gravity.
The ultimate suck-up.

02:20.457 --> 02:24.292
(chuckles) Can't spell "gravity"
without "gravy."

02:24.311 --> 02:26.219
(chuckles)
Have some more.

02:26.313 --> 02:28.630
(gulps, sighs)

02:28.649 --> 02:31.966
The subject I have chosen
for my mobile is this lady.

02:32.027 --> 02:33.043
Ta-da!

02:33.103 --> 02:36.321
Of course. Yes. Her. Absolutely.

02:36.473 --> 02:40.934
The woman who lives
at the center of the Earth.

02:41.086 --> 02:42.828
It's Gladys West,
the mathematician

02:43.021 --> 02:47.073
whose work in satellite geodesy
helped create GPS.

02:47.168 --> 02:51.077
GPS. The invention that killed
the "I got lost" excuse.

02:51.172 --> 02:53.839
Oh, gee, I'm sorry, Marge.

02:54.032 --> 02:57.734
I just can't find the restaurant
for your sisters' birthday.

02:57.753 --> 03:00.995
<i> GPS:</i>
<i> Your destination is</i>
<i> 60 feet ahead.</i>

03:01.056 --> 03:02.163
Shut up.

03:02.224 --> 03:03.548
<i> 40 feet ahead.</i>

03:03.684 --> 03:04.999
Shut up!

03:05.019 --> 03:06.518
<i> 20 feet ahead.</i>

03:06.711 --> 03:09.095
Just what I need: another woman
who's always right.

03:09.248 --> 03:12.916
<i> You have now arrived at</i>
<i> Lovely Ladies Cigar Lounge.</i>

03:14.069 --> 03:17.604
You'll be cutting and serving
the us-shaped cake.

03:17.756 --> 03:19.847
-(laughs)
-Who wants a thigh?

03:19.909 --> 03:23.443
Curse you, Gladys West!

03:23.537 --> 03:25.204
-(scoffs)
-Dad, please!

03:25.355 --> 03:27.855
This mobile could be
my ticket into Yale.

03:27.917 --> 03:29.950
Another Bush kid.
Another Bush kid.

03:30.085 --> 03:32.118
How about this girl?

03:32.213 --> 03:34.287
Her grades and test scores
are superb.

03:34.381 --> 03:36.106
She's got boola.

03:36.166 --> 03:38.625
But does she have "Boola Boola"?

03:38.719 --> 03:41.720
What about this mobile
she did in the second grade?

03:41.871 --> 03:43.889
Accept. Full ride.

03:44.082 --> 03:47.300
♪<i> Boola Boola,</i>
<i> Boola Boola...</i> ♪

03:47.394 --> 03:50.562
Ah, wha-- how did I get here?

03:50.714 --> 03:52.806
They say it's dangerous
to wake up someone

03:52.900 --> 03:55.049
who's dreaming of Yale.

03:55.069 --> 03:58.052
Well, just so I'm covered,
let me dream of a safety school.

03:58.072 --> 04:00.647
(snores)
UMass Amherst.

04:00.741 --> 04:02.890
UMass Amherst.

04:02.952 --> 04:03.891
(snores)

04:03.953 --> 04:05.244
(school bell rings)

04:06.472 --> 04:08.247
Is Miss Hoover out sick?

04:08.440 --> 04:10.807
No, I'm in sick.

04:10.826 --> 04:12.642
I sprained a disc in my back.

04:12.703 --> 04:14.327
It feels like I'm passing
a kidney stone

04:14.480 --> 04:15.921
while giving birth.

04:16.114 --> 04:18.498
I say "excuse me"
when I give burps.

04:18.650 --> 04:20.150
Not the same, Ralph.

04:20.168 --> 04:22.261
Fortunately, my new
Teaching With Stylus tablet

04:22.454 --> 04:25.264
lets me run the classroom
from any position.

04:25.457 --> 04:28.100
(sighs) Let's get inspired.

04:28.293 --> 04:30.084
You might think
"German chocolate cake"

04:30.187 --> 04:32.996
originated in Germany, but<i> nein.</i>

04:33.056 --> 04:36.500
Actually, it was invented
by an American mill worker

04:36.560 --> 04:38.835
named Samuel German.

04:38.854 --> 04:40.112
(all gasp)

04:40.263 --> 04:43.507
I'm from America
but my measles are German.

04:43.525 --> 04:46.526
I'm inspired by
<i> The Masked Singer</i> and...

04:46.620 --> 04:49.454
It doesn't come off. Help!

04:49.647 --> 04:54.334
Help! Help...!

04:56.246 --> 04:58.355
I know these presentations
are boring

04:58.415 --> 05:00.357
and everyone hates them, so...

05:00.417 --> 05:01.691
-You're gonna stop?
-Better.

05:01.752 --> 05:03.242
I'm gonna rap.

05:03.304 --> 05:05.220
(all groan)

05:06.223 --> 05:08.724
(rapper beatboxing)

05:10.702 --> 05:12.293
♪ ♪

05:12.313 --> 05:14.888
♪<i> Ah-ha-ha-ha, Gladys West,</i>
<i> Gladys West</i> ♪

05:15.040 --> 05:16.589
♪<i> If you don't know</i>
<i> where you're goin'</i> ♪

05:16.741 --> 05:18.241
♪<i> She'll make sure your car</i>
<i> don't get a towin'</i> ♪

05:18.243 --> 05:19.801
♪<i> Satellite telemetry,</i>
<i> should've been in ebony</i> ♪

05:19.820 --> 05:21.653
♪<i> When it comes to geodesy,</i>
<i> she's got mad skills</i> ♪

05:21.763 --> 05:24.064
-♪<i> Like Yeezy</i> ♪
-♪<i> We're giving props to</i> ♪

05:24.216 --> 05:25.398
♪<i> Gladys West</i> ♪

05:25.492 --> 05:27.400
♪<i> We're giving props</i> ♪

05:27.494 --> 05:30.053
♪<i> 'Cause she's the best</i> ♪

05:30.113 --> 05:31.663
-Lisa.
-♪<i> Doo-doo-doo-doo</i> ♪

05:31.856 --> 05:33.147
♪<i> Doo-doo-doo</i> ♪

05:33.167 --> 05:35.149
Lisa, you're over
your two-minute limit.

05:35.252 --> 05:37.577
♪<i> Doo-doo-doo-doo, doo-doo-doo</i> ♪

05:37.671 --> 05:40.339
That's enough.
Ralph, you're up.

05:40.490 --> 05:42.507
My hero is my thumb.

05:42.700 --> 05:45.660
It has its own room in
my mittens. Thank you.

05:45.679 --> 05:47.179
Okay. That's it.

05:47.372 --> 05:49.723
Now put the supplements
to your reports on my desk.

05:55.064 --> 05:56.980
Give me a sec
to post the grades.

06:00.218 --> 06:02.527
A B-minus? No, no.

06:02.720 --> 06:06.031
This can't be right.
This can't be right.

06:06.182 --> 06:09.109
The same grade as Ralph?!
Sorry, Ralph, no offense.

06:09.261 --> 06:11.444
There's "a fence" around my bed

06:11.538 --> 06:14.931
so I don't steal things
from Daddy's squad car again.

06:14.950 --> 06:17.617
<i> LOU:</i>
<i> Chief, did you tell Snake he</i>
<i> could have jail outside today?</i>

06:17.769 --> 06:18.768
<i>'Cause that's what he's saying.</i>

06:18.787 --> 06:20.361
<i> WIGGUM:</i>
<i> Leave me alone.</i>

06:20.422 --> 06:22.381
Listen, Miss "took too long
on her presentation,"

06:22.574 --> 06:24.958
it's not only right, it's easy

06:25.052 --> 06:27.961
with my "Select All"
B-minus option.

06:28.055 --> 06:30.964
Miss Hoover, this is so unfair.

06:31.058 --> 06:34.059
I come here every day
eager to learn

06:34.252 --> 06:37.137
and you just put me down

06:37.289 --> 06:39.231
and complain about your job.

06:39.424 --> 06:41.141
In the end, what are you?

06:41.235 --> 06:43.384
You're just somebody
who works off a formula

06:43.487 --> 06:45.404
that leaves no room for passion,

06:45.572 --> 06:47.572
individual effort,

06:47.765 --> 06:50.057
or the process
of learning itself.

06:50.077 --> 06:51.392
-Mm.
-In other words,

06:51.453 --> 06:54.036
you're an uninspiring hack!

06:54.139 --> 06:57.140
Apologize immediately.

06:57.200 --> 06:59.918
No. I told the truth.

07:00.111 --> 07:02.979
The truth has no place
in this classroom.

07:03.039 --> 07:05.315
Lisa, go to detention.

07:05.375 --> 07:07.801
(echoing):
Detention. Detention. Detention.

07:16.628 --> 07:19.829
One pencil with nervous
teeth marks.

07:19.848 --> 07:23.424
One spelling bee
winner's ribbon, faded.

07:23.444 --> 07:26.111
One quarter ounce of marijuana.

07:26.304 --> 07:28.188
Those are pencil shavings.

07:28.340 --> 07:31.007
Willie's water pipe
will be the judge of that.

07:31.067 --> 07:33.577
♪ ♪

07:44.131 --> 07:47.424
-(spitball ricochets)
-♪ ♪

08:03.984 --> 08:05.817
Look at those arms.

08:05.986 --> 08:08.820
Blank canvas
for a Sharpie tattoo.

08:10.607 --> 08:13.049
Um, I'm actually a vegetarian.
(laughs nervously)

08:13.068 --> 08:15.552
Okay, how do you feel
about beets?

08:15.612 --> 08:18.497
Ooh, is this one of those
questions that sets me up

08:18.690 --> 08:19.723
to get punched?

08:19.783 --> 08:21.649
Only one way to find out.

08:21.710 --> 08:23.835
Yeah, tell us
your opinion of beets.

08:24.028 --> 08:25.837
BART:
Leave her alone, you jackals.

08:26.030 --> 08:28.155
♪ ♪

08:28.258 --> 08:30.675
This is the largest stink bomb
they make.

08:30.868 --> 08:33.178
So powerful it could only
be developed by a scientist

08:33.371 --> 08:35.329
without a nose.

08:35.390 --> 08:37.407
How did he know it worked?

08:37.425 --> 08:39.684
He smelled it... with his ears.

08:39.877 --> 08:42.095
-Whoa.
-Uh-oh.
-Oh.

08:42.189 --> 08:44.189
And that girl's with me.

08:44.382 --> 08:45.506
Whoa!

08:46.184 --> 08:48.360
Well, well, well.
Together at last.

08:48.553 --> 08:50.344
I didn't do anything wrong.

08:50.405 --> 08:53.590
Miss Hoover should be
in detention, not me.

08:53.608 --> 08:55.200
There is a detention
for teachers.

08:55.393 --> 08:56.760
It's called being a teacher.

08:56.820 --> 08:58.778
Now, let me show you my world.

08:58.872 --> 09:00.539
Lots of gangs will recruit you:

09:00.732 --> 09:02.448
The Magnificent Seven-Year-Olds.

09:02.584 --> 09:05.526
Tardy Incorporated.
Hell's Angles.

09:05.546 --> 09:07.587
(excited murmuring)

09:09.216 --> 09:13.626
My greatest weapon is inside
my head. My mucus.

09:13.779 --> 09:15.554
Ms. Timberwood!

09:15.747 --> 09:17.705
In here, she doesn't know you.

09:17.724 --> 09:19.558
She used to call me Sunshine.

09:19.751 --> 09:21.393
I call all the girls Sunshine.

09:21.562 --> 09:23.970
I call all the boys Joe Cool.

09:24.064 --> 09:26.623
Oh, you said I was
the only Joe Cool!

09:26.725 --> 09:28.458
-(grunts)
-(sniffs)

09:28.518 --> 09:31.978
That's actually lavender,
so, thank you.

09:32.072 --> 09:33.530
BART:
<i> !Ay caramba!</i>

09:34.575 --> 09:36.491
(sobbing):
No...!

09:41.105 --> 09:43.248
(sniffles)
No dinner for me.

09:43.441 --> 09:45.250
I'm too miserable to eat again.

09:45.419 --> 09:47.586
This is pretty rough on me, too.

09:49.781 --> 09:51.047
(sobbing)

09:52.301 --> 09:53.817
(muffled sobbing)

09:53.918 --> 09:56.319
Please pull the covers off.

09:56.421 --> 10:00.448
No, I don't want to live
in the world above the covers.

10:00.517 --> 10:01.641
(sighs)

10:03.270 --> 10:06.329
I worked so hard on my mobile.

10:06.389 --> 10:09.608
I know. And Miss Hoover
wasn't very nice.

10:09.801 --> 10:11.684
Thank you, Mom.

10:11.837 --> 10:13.353
But you weren't very nice,
either.

10:13.488 --> 10:14.446
What?!

10:14.639 --> 10:16.189
Hey, are we camping out here?

10:16.325 --> 10:18.508
Because I have a great
campfire story.

10:18.568 --> 10:21.694
About a man betrayed
by his own hand.

10:21.788 --> 10:24.438
What the...?
Oh, oh, my God, it's you!

10:24.499 --> 10:27.292
(choking)

10:27.443 --> 10:29.443
-Homer.
-Yes, Marge.

10:29.504 --> 10:33.189
I was going to encourage
Lisa to apologize.

10:33.291 --> 10:34.615
But I shouldn't have to.

10:34.676 --> 10:37.043
Women say "I'm sorry" constantly

10:37.137 --> 10:39.212
because men make us feel like
we have to apologize

10:39.348 --> 10:40.621
for existing

10:40.682 --> 10:43.032
while they do
whatever they like.

10:43.093 --> 10:44.701
Yo. Milhouse is sleepin' over.

10:44.761 --> 10:46.386
-Awesome.
-Huh?

10:46.521 --> 10:47.687
(Lisa groans)

10:49.524 --> 10:50.890
Wah!

10:50.984 --> 10:53.042
Ready to apologize, Lisa?

10:53.103 --> 10:54.986
We both know
what's at stake here.

10:58.441 --> 11:00.659
Not so fast, Lisa.

11:00.810 --> 11:03.477
You didn't apologize
to your second grade teacher,

11:03.538 --> 11:06.389
and all we do at Yale
is apologize.

11:06.449 --> 11:09.483
♪<i> Sorry, sorry, sorry</i> ♪

11:09.544 --> 11:12.729
♪<i> Please excuse our quirks</i> ♪

11:12.747 --> 11:14.580
♪<i> Quirks, quirks, quirks</i> ♪

11:14.675 --> 11:17.583
♪<i> Won't you kindly listen</i> ♪

11:17.719 --> 11:21.254
♪<i> To us rich male jerks?</i> ♪

11:21.390 --> 11:25.517
♪<i> We sing for free.</i> ♪

11:28.689 --> 11:31.022
(shivering)

11:31.215 --> 11:34.526
Okay, Lisa, your future is
in my hands.

11:34.719 --> 11:37.862
I'm-I'm...<i> not</i> sorry!

11:38.014 --> 11:39.605
I'm just glad
I won't have you next year

11:39.700 --> 11:41.107
as a teacher.

11:41.259 --> 11:44.185
I might just move to third grade
to torment you.

11:44.246 --> 11:47.280
That would be a real hack move.

11:47.374 --> 11:48.781
Ugh!

11:48.875 --> 11:50.834
Freshen it up.

11:52.212 --> 11:53.545
Love it.

11:58.334 --> 12:00.626
Personally, I never say
I'm sorry.

12:00.721 --> 12:03.221
I say "I'm soggy."
Teachers hear what they want.

12:03.414 --> 12:06.449
Bart Simpson, did you glue
these recorders together?

12:06.468 --> 12:07.633
Soggy.

12:07.728 --> 12:09.969
-Forgiven.
-And Willie can use it

12:10.121 --> 12:11.896
to whack the hornets' nests.

12:12.089 --> 12:14.381
-(hornets buzzing)
-(grunting)

12:14.401 --> 12:16.476
Yeah, come on and fight me
like a man.

12:16.570 --> 12:18.294
(grunting)

12:18.313 --> 12:20.646
Uh, which one of you does
the negotiating?

12:20.741 --> 12:22.407
Miss Hoover?

12:22.558 --> 12:24.300
(clears throat)
In reference to our

12:24.360 --> 12:27.078
recent difficulty,
I would just like to say

12:27.271 --> 12:28.638
I'm soggy.

12:28.698 --> 12:31.324
Did you just say "I'm soggy"?

12:31.476 --> 12:33.752
In addition to a hack,
you must think I'm a fool.

12:33.945 --> 12:36.145
-Double detention.
-(gasps)

12:36.206 --> 12:39.482
♪<i> Who's soggy now?</i> ♪

12:39.542 --> 12:41.150
And that counts
as your music education

12:41.252 --> 12:43.077
for the semester.

12:43.096 --> 12:45.488
Feels kind of funny driving
<i> you</i> home from detention.

12:45.590 --> 12:47.156
(chuckles)

12:47.175 --> 12:48.933
Yeah, well, it's gonna
take me a few minutes

12:49.126 --> 12:51.418
to get used to being
on the outside.

12:51.438 --> 12:54.163
Honey, play the ad
I forwarded you.

12:54.224 --> 12:55.774
<i> ANNOUNCER:</i>
<i> Having trouble with</i>
<i> a relationship?</i>

12:55.967 --> 12:58.259
<i> Come to the Springfield</i>
<i> Education Annex.</i>

12:58.320 --> 13:00.670
<i> We'll teach you how to</i>
<i> communicate honestly,</i>

13:00.730 --> 13:02.338
<i> how to lie convincingly,</i>

13:02.398 --> 13:04.932
<i> and how to apologize</i>
<i> and mostly mean it.</i>

13:04.993 --> 13:06.509
Apologize?

13:06.569 --> 13:08.361
<i> Springfield Education Annex,</i>

13:08.513 --> 13:10.437
<i> located in the third abandoned</i>
<i> mall on Route One.</i>

13:10.499 --> 13:12.348
<i> Don't park at the Greek church</i>
<i> across the street.</i>

13:12.367 --> 13:14.033
<i> We're in a feud with them.</i>

13:14.127 --> 13:16.869
<i> There's nothing orthodox about</i>
<i> how fast they tow.</i>

13:16.963 --> 13:19.446
So, when apologizing
from your heart,

13:19.466 --> 13:23.117
saying sorry allows
the healing process to begin.

13:23.178 --> 13:25.286
-Sorry I'm late.
-What?!
-She's sorry?

13:25.347 --> 13:27.329
Yeah, I've heard that one a lot.

13:27.390 --> 13:29.032
Well, I don't mind
saying I'm sorry

13:29.092 --> 13:30.383
when it's appropriate.

13:30.519 --> 13:33.036
Appropriate.
Never heard of that word.

13:33.096 --> 13:35.054
I know "inappropriate."

13:35.190 --> 13:36.964
-True. So true.
-Oh, yes, yes.

13:37.025 --> 13:40.059
Now, to truly apologize,
I find it helps

13:40.211 --> 13:43.470
to look at the world from
the other person's perspective.

13:43.532 --> 13:44.989
Now, repeat after me.

13:45.158 --> 13:47.325
I will not judge someone
until I walk a mile

13:47.518 --> 13:49.218
in their shoes.

13:49.279 --> 13:51.496
I will not judge someone until

13:51.689 --> 13:55.408
I walk a mile in their shoes.

13:55.502 --> 13:57.836
Well, what's the matter
with the rest of you?

13:58.029 --> 13:59.912
Walk a mile? Please.

14:00.090 --> 14:02.048
Like, over how many years?

14:03.218 --> 14:04.551
(school bell rings)

14:06.203 --> 14:07.679
Huh?

14:07.872 --> 14:10.089
Miss Hoover takes the bus.
I didn't know that.

14:10.225 --> 14:12.016
Actually, she takes two buses.

14:12.209 --> 14:14.185
Then she walks half a mile
down a train track,

14:14.354 --> 14:16.187
swings across a drainage ditch

14:16.339 --> 14:19.248
and rides a piece of cardboard
down a hill to help her back.

14:19.350 --> 14:22.418
-Oh, that's terrible.
-I guess.

14:22.520 --> 14:25.922
You learn a lot of sad things
when you sell weed to teachers.

14:26.024 --> 14:27.757
Make it a double.

14:27.859 --> 14:29.659
I'll be in the ball shed.

14:41.623 --> 14:44.957
-Excuse me, are you
Jennifer Aniston?
-No.

14:45.110 --> 14:48.720
That's exactly what
Jennifer Aniston would say.

14:48.889 --> 14:52.181
♪ ♪

15:02.819 --> 15:05.403
Oh... Dear Lord,

15:05.554 --> 15:07.146
please grant me this winner.

15:07.240 --> 15:10.816
I lost. And my quarter broke.

15:10.911 --> 15:12.468
Gee.

15:12.528 --> 15:15.079
♪ ♪

15:15.272 --> 15:16.497
-(grunting)
-(back cracking)

15:19.419 --> 15:21.419
Aw.

15:32.790 --> 15:35.158
Yeah, I'm the super.
What are you doing here?

15:35.218 --> 15:37.084
Uh, I'm one of Miss Hoover's
students,

15:37.145 --> 15:39.345
and I just want to
understand her life.

15:39.497 --> 15:40.830
All right, come on in.

15:40.890 --> 15:43.499
How can I say no
to a sweet face like yours, huh?

15:43.559 --> 15:47.019
Yeah, um, I have some business
in 12-A.

15:47.155 --> 15:51.157
Yeah, how can I say no
to a sweet face like yours?

15:52.977 --> 15:54.786
Here, Hemsworth, come cuddle.

15:54.979 --> 15:56.603
(cat mewls defiantly)

15:56.665 --> 15:58.790
I'm so alone.
(sighs)

15:58.941 --> 16:01.033
Just don't eat me when I die.

16:01.127 --> 16:03.352
(mewls oddly)

16:03.413 --> 16:05.688
(gasps)
Is someone at the door?

16:05.748 --> 16:07.523
I-I can't turn my head.

16:07.583 --> 16:08.949
(sobs quietly)

16:09.052 --> 16:11.452
There's a great blues song
in here,

16:11.513 --> 16:13.696
but I don't know what it is.

16:13.756 --> 16:17.558
-Don't you drag us
into your problems.
-(crying)

16:22.190 --> 16:24.348
Dad, I'm ready to say I'm sorry,

16:24.484 --> 16:26.058
but now it's not enough.

16:26.152 --> 16:28.044
Lisa, you just gotta be sincere.

16:28.104 --> 16:30.304
If you have a disagreement
with another driver,

16:30.365 --> 16:33.549
you simply say, "I'm sorry.
Please go ahead."

16:33.609 --> 16:36.569
Then you follow 'em home
and you pee in their gas tank.

16:36.663 --> 16:38.070
You<i> pee</i> in there!

16:38.164 --> 16:40.164
Just can't say "I'm sorry."

16:40.357 --> 16:42.483
Does that remind you
of anyone, Carl?

16:42.585 --> 16:44.318
Oh, God, not this again.

16:44.379 --> 16:46.504
I have nothing to apologize for.

16:46.697 --> 16:49.173
You had 20 years
to watch<i> The Sixth Sense.</i>

16:49.366 --> 16:51.175
That's beyond
the spoiler window.

16:51.368 --> 16:53.511
Oh, so it's okay for me
to tell you

16:53.704 --> 16:56.014
that the Lady Gaga<i> Star</i>
<i> is Born</i> is exactly the same

16:56.165 --> 16:57.348
as all the other<i> Star is Borns?</i>

16:57.541 --> 17:00.501
(gasps)
I'll kill you. I'll kill you!

17:00.562 --> 17:02.311
Goodbye, college fund.

17:06.350 --> 17:08.417
(grunts, crying)

17:08.436 --> 17:11.529
You were gonna pay
for my mini fridge.

17:13.182 --> 17:15.424
I need to put a down payment
on something for someone

17:15.485 --> 17:17.760
I really owe an apology to.

17:17.820 --> 17:20.705
A framed movie poster for
<i> The Three Amigos?</i>

17:20.856 --> 17:22.598
It's better than you remember.

17:22.658 --> 17:25.451
-No.
-All right, how about
school supplies?

17:25.603 --> 17:28.838
I got a Scottish guy who
sells 'em to me every week.

17:30.291 --> 17:31.440
Hi, Willie.

17:31.501 --> 17:34.627
Uh, uh,<i> yo no hablo</i> English.

17:34.721 --> 17:36.462
Ach, the English.

17:36.614 --> 17:38.848
How I hate those wankers.

17:43.254 --> 17:45.563
Shh, shh, shh.
She's coming. She's coming.

17:45.756 --> 17:47.231
(gasps)

17:47.424 --> 17:50.401
-Have a seat. Top of the line.
-Oh...

17:50.594 --> 17:52.612
I can see your faces again.

17:52.739 --> 17:55.147
And now my favorite.
The ceiling.

17:55.241 --> 17:59.410
Miss Hoover, I'm sorry
I made your life harder,

17:59.603 --> 18:02.488
and I hope this chair
makes it easier.

18:02.582 --> 18:05.399
Well, I don't accept
your apology.

18:05.418 --> 18:07.251
-What?
-What am I supposed to do

18:07.444 --> 18:09.069
after you called me a hack?

18:09.130 --> 18:11.405
In retrospect,
I might have been wrong.

18:11.466 --> 18:13.666
The sad truth is apologies
can come too late

18:13.818 --> 18:15.409
to do any good.

18:15.470 --> 18:19.746
Congratulations, you just
learned something from my class.

18:19.808 --> 18:21.324
I guess what you've learned is

18:21.384 --> 18:23.750
teachers shouldn't get tenure.

18:23.812 --> 18:26.329
There has to be
a better lesson from this.

18:26.389 --> 18:27.830
There has to.

18:27.890 --> 18:30.182
You've planted a seed, sweetie.

18:30.335 --> 18:32.835
-The seed will grow.
-Amen.

18:32.895 --> 18:35.338
Why is everyone on the roof?

18:35.398 --> 18:36.948
(doorbell ringing)

18:37.141 --> 18:40.343
I know you're in there.
I'm old, but I'm not dead.

18:40.403 --> 18:42.194
Or is it the other way around?

18:42.347 --> 18:44.363
(doorbell ringing)

18:44.457 --> 18:46.773
What does this do?

18:46.793 --> 18:49.109
-(vibrating)
-Oh, that's a surprise.

18:49.170 --> 18:52.037
(moans):
Really quite nice.

18:52.132 --> 18:53.689
Oh, yeah.

18:53.791 --> 18:56.041
Miss Hoover, I've been thinking,

18:56.136 --> 18:58.785
and no offense,
but I bought you a chair.

18:58.805 --> 19:01.197
And that's really hard
for an eight-year-old.

19:01.257 --> 19:03.549
-All is forgiven.
-How forgiven?

19:03.685 --> 19:05.050
B-plus.

19:05.186 --> 19:06.202
I'll take it.

19:06.262 --> 19:08.037
Can I get a B-plus, too?

19:08.097 --> 19:09.522
-Sure.
-D'oh.

19:11.484 --> 19:13.225
-I'm soggy.
-Listen, boy.

19:13.319 --> 19:15.561
I'm on to you. I know
you're saying "soggy,"

19:15.655 --> 19:16.654
not "sorry." Mm.

19:16.823 --> 19:18.322
You're right, you're right.

19:18.491 --> 19:20.549
I completely apolo-cheese.

19:20.610 --> 19:22.326
-What?
-I beg your par-ton.

19:22.519 --> 19:25.054
-Come again?
-Guilty as Marged.

19:25.114 --> 19:27.331
I'll accept that.

19:27.483 --> 19:29.458
-Soggy.
-Enough already.

19:34.048 --> 19:36.065
♪<i> Lisa's at Yale</i> ♪

19:36.067 --> 19:39.177
♪<i> She'll never fail</i> ♪

19:39.370 --> 19:43.681
♪<i> She's got a huge</i>
<i> college debt</i> ♪

19:43.832 --> 19:46.425
♪<i> Debt, debt</i> ♪

19:46.519 --> 19:49.336
Please, I'm trying to study!

19:49.397 --> 19:53.649
♪<i> Then go to Brown.</i> ♪

19:55.753 --> 19:57.753
Um, can I have the book back?

19:57.855 --> 19:59.906
It cost $200.

20:08.249 --> 20:13.193
Now to dream of being
a World War I flying ace.

20:13.213 --> 20:15.955
(imitating engines roaring)

20:16.090 --> 20:19.050
(imitating gunfire)

20:19.219 --> 20:21.219
(gunfire)

20:29.062 --> 20:31.062
(moans sadly)

